One person has died and 14 have been injured after a car and a taxi collided on a district road in Swayimane, Wartburg on Tuesday afternoon. ER24 and local authorities were on scene. According to ER24, they found the taxi and car on the same side of the road. “Several people were found seated and lying near the vehicles. We assessed the patients and found a man from the light motor vehicle had sustained fatal injuries,” reads their statement. Meanwhile, 14 other patients suffered minor to moderate injuries and were treated and later taken to nearby hospitals. SAPS will be investigating further details surrounding the incident.